# Title: Potential Unquoted Service Path Reconnaissance Via Wmic.EXE
# Author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
# Date: 2022-06-20
# Level: medium
# Description: Detects known WMI recon method to look for unquoted service paths using wmic. Often used by pentester and attacker enumeration scripts
# MITRE Tactic: Execution
# Tags: attack.execution, attack.t1047
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_wmic_recon_unquoted_service_search.yml

CommandLine="* service get *" CommandLine="*name,displayname,pathname,startmode*" OriginalFileName="wmic.exe" OR Image="*\\WMIC.exe"